<manpage>
    <sample url="sdk\operating_system\crt\libc\ctype\isspace">isspace</sample>
    <title>isspace iswspace</title>
    <volume>C Run-Time Library</volume>
    <routine_idx> ctype_idx.htm </routine_idx>

    <description>
        <para>Returns true if c is a whitespace character. In the standard "C" locale, isspace returns true only for the standard whitespace characters, which are ' ' space, '\f' formfeed, '\n' newline, '\r' carriage return, '\t' horizontal tab, '\v' vertical tab.</para>
    </description>

    <syntax>
        <return_val>int</return_val>
        <func_name>isspace</func_name>
        <parameters>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>int</param_type>
                <param_name>c</param_name>
                <param_note>
                    <para>input integer</para>
                </param_note>
            </func_param>
        </parameters>
    </syntax>

    <return>
        <para>If c is a whitespace character (0x09 - 0x0D or 0x20),then isspace returns a non-zero value. It returns 0 if c does not satisfy the test condition.</para>
    </return>

    <requirements>
        <routine>
            <routine_name>isspace</routine_name>
            <headerfile>ctype.h</headerfile>
            <compatibility>ANSI, Windows 2000, Elastos 2.0</compatibility>
        </routine>
    </requirements>

    <example>
<pre>
//==========================================================================
// Copyright (c) 2000-2004,  Elastos, Inc.  All Rights Reserved.
//==========================================================================

/* isspace.cpp: This program uses isspace to verify c
 * whether it is a space character (0x09 ¨C 0x0D or 0x20).
 */

#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;ctype.h&gt;

int main()
{
    int c = 0x09;
    if (isspace(c)) {
        printf(&quot;it is a particular representation of a &quot;
            &quot;space character.\n&quot;);
    }
    else {
        printf(&quot;it is not a particular representation of a &quot;
            &quot;space character.\n&quot;);
    }

    return 0;
}
</pre>
    </example>
<result>
it is a particular representation of a space character.
</result>



